WIDGETS

Kryon provides 89 widget types. Every widget is represented as a directory 
in the /wm namespace. Properties are files within that directory.

CORE PROPERTIES (Mandatory for all)

    type        (string, RO)    Widget type name
    rect        (string)        "x y w h" (Pixels in Display mode, Cells in TTY)
    visible     (int)           0 (hidden) or 1 (visible)
    enabled     (int)           0 (disabled) or 1 (active)
    mode_hint   (string)        "auto", "gui-only", "tui-only"

COMMON PROPERTIES

    text        (string)        Label, caption, or content
    value       (string)        Current state/data (e.g., "1" for checked)
    placeholder (string)        Hint text for empty inputs
    tooltip     (string)        Hover/focus description



WIDGET CATALOG (89 TOTAL)

Input (24):
    TextInput, PasswordInput, TextArea, SearchInput, NumberInput, 
    EmailInput, UrlInput, TelInput, Checkbox, RadioButton, Dropdown, 
    MultiSelect, ListBox, Switch, Slider, RangeSlider, Rating, Spinbox, 
    DateInput, TimeInput, DateTimeInput, MonthInput, WeekInput, FileInput

Buttons (8):
    Button, SubmitButton, ResetButton, IconButton, 
    FloatingActionButton, DropdownButton, SegmentedControl, ToolButton

Display (11):
    Label, Heading, Paragraph, RichText, Code, Image, 
    ProgressBar, ActivityIndicator, Badge, Divider, Tooltip

Containers (11):
    Container, Box, Frame, Card, ScrollArea, SplitPane, 
    TabContainer, Dialog, Modal, ActionSheet, Drawer

Lists (8):
    ListItem, ListTile, ListView, GridView, DataTable, 
    TreeView, Chip, Tag

Navigation (8):
    MenuBar, ToolBar, NavBar, NavRail, Breadcrumb, 
    Pagination, Stepper, PageView

Menus (4):
    DropdownMenu, ContextMenu, CascadingMenu, PopupMenu

Forms (4):
    Form, FormGroup, ValidationMessage, InputGroup

Windows (4): (Used within the /win/ hierarchy)
    Window, DialogWindow, PageScaffold, Fullscreen

Specialized (7):
    Canvas, Svg, Chart, ColorPicker, SignaturePad, Resizable, Calendar

Terminal/Low-Level (1):
    Terminal (provides a virtual /dev/cons for the widget)



LAYOUT SYSTEM

Container widgets manage the 'rect' of their children automatically unless 
set to "absolute".

    layout      (string)    "row", "column", "grid", "stack", "absolute"
    gap         (int)       Spacing between children (pixels or cells)
    padding     (int)       Internal border spacing
    align       (string)    "start", "center", "end", "stretch"
    justify     (string)    "start", "center", "end", "space-between"

TTY DEGRADATION STRATEGY

When Kryon is in TTY mode, widgets map to character approximations:
- ProgressBar: [====>    ]
- Checkbox: [X] or [ ]
- Button: < Text >
- Layouts: Grid cells map 1:1 to terminal character coordinates.

EVENTS

Events are read-only streams from the 'events' file of each widget.

    clicked x=50 y=20 button=1
    changed value="updated text"
    mouse_enter / mouse_leave
    focus_gained / focus_lost
    key_press key=Enter